Police stormed politician Jackson Kibor's home on Tuesday and arrested him for misusing his gun. Kibor shot three times at his son Ezekiel last Wednesday in a dispute over their farm near Eldoret. He said he did so in self-defence but his son claimed he intended to kill.More on this: Jackson Kibor under probe for shooting at son in land disputeEldoret East OCPD Samwel Mutunga led the operation to arrest the veteran politician who is also a farmer. He said Kibor, who was taken to Eldoret police station,&nbsp;will be charged with misuse of a firearm. Kibor has been involved in a dispute with four of his sons over ownership of the 1,250-acre farm where the incident occurred.&nbsp;Also read: Jackson Kibor facing arrest, firearm misuse charge after shooting at son